post_text: Fewer students than expected rode the buses at the elementary today. Because of that, our plan for pick up and drop off did not go as expected. We apologize for all of the delays. In order to alleviate the congestion, we have a revised plan. Pre-K through 2nd grade will pick up and drop off in front of the the school at 2:50 pm. 3rd through 5th grade students will also pick up and drop off in front of the school at 3:20 pm. Please note that if you have a child who gets out at 2:50 pm, you can not sit and wait in the parking lot. The line has to continue moving. Head start will continue to pick up and drop off behind the school. Thank you for your patience and for contributing to an overall great first day!

post_text:
Elementary Parents,

We are changing our drop off and pick up procedures this year. The school building will open at 7:30 for all students. Headstart through 2nd grade will dismiss at 2:50. 3rd through 5th grade will dismiss at 3:20. Busses will run at 2:50 for 2nd grade and below and 3:20 for 3rd-5th grade. All students who are car riders will be dropped off and picked up in the back of the school by the cafeteria. Parents will need to enter from Crescent Lane and follow the drive to exit onto City View Drive. We ask that parents remain in the cars and wait for students to come to them. Students will be waiting in the cafeteria and will be called to the car by a staff member. Only busses will be dropping off and picking up in the front entrance. A map showing the path for drop off and pick up will be available shortly on the elementary section of our new parent resource website available here: https://sites.google.com/cityview-isd.net/family-resources/district-information

City View Elementary Registration for Pre-K, Kindergarten, and New Students will be by appointment only on August 4th, 5th, and 6th. Please complete the attached form to sign up for a time.

* Parents will be required to follow social distancing and anyone over the age of 10 will be required to wear a mask.

* Parents will need to bring the following documents:
* Birth Certificate
* Social Security Card
* Proof of residency (like lease agreement or utility bill)

* Pre-k students will also need to bring a proof of income.

* Please fill out the online enrollment which is posted on the school website under "For Parents-> Student Enrollment and Registration" prior to appointment.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May.

The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Please see handout documents here - https://drive.google.com/open?id=1eiViDQWU6j-57v2KAJ70gLz551Bh93ac

post_text:
The governor is supposed to give school districts more guidance on graduation ceremonies within the week, so these plans could change.

Graduation will take place on the City View ISD football field on Saturday, May 23rd at 9:00 a.m.

We don't know at this time how many spectator tickets each senior will receive, but we will do our best to get them as many as possible. I don't want to say how many tickets each senior will receive until the governor gives us some direction. Our plan as of now is to designate that each senior's family will have one row of bleachers to themselves. Seniors will draw for rows at graduation practice on May 22nd. We plan on to broadcast the graduation live on a social media outlet, if possible. Graduates, teachers, and the CV band will be seated on the football field during the ceremony.

If for some reason the governor doesn't allow us to have graduation on May 23rd, we will try again on Saturday, June 6th.

Thank you,

Tony Bushong

post_text:
COVID-19 UPDATE (4/17/2020)

The governor just closed schools for the remainder of the year. I know this is very disheartening to many as we will finish out the year instructing students using distance learning. As of right now, we have no plans of cancelling graduation. Even if we have to postpone for a month or two, the plan will be to have graduation. Our seniors deserve the right to walk across the stage and receive their diplomas and we are going to do our best to make that happen. I will get back with you when I receive more information.

Tony Bushong

post_text: The City View Elementary meet the teacher night that was scheduled for 4:30 - 6:30 PM today has been cancelled due to a water main break outside of the campus. The Junior/Senior High meet the teacher will continue as scheduled from 5:00 - 7:00 PM.
